messages.content: Do you know the address of your house?
Can you ask your mommy what the address is?
Hello? Is your mom, can your mommy talk?
No, she can't talk now. She's up down.
Is she laying down on the ground?
Okay, do you know what your house looks like?
White? Okay, what color is your driveway?
Hang on, Kevin, just a second. It's white.
White cars in front of your house?
I can't do such as a... White car. Because I'm trying to get dresses from a little bit of a girl. I only have one white car, and Daddy has a big black car.
Big black car? Okay. Do you have any dogs or anything in your yard?
We have a big giant one. A big car.
Three? Okay. You're going to have to help me so we can get the ambulance there to help your mommy, okay?
Can you go to the door and turn on the porch light so the ambulance can find the house?
Stay on the phone with me. Don't put the phone down, okay? What is your name?
Oh, okay. Do you have a baby brother?
Did you turn on the porch light for me?
Okay, I'll let you know when to open up the front door, okay?
Okay, we'll have to watch for the ambulance, and you'll have to help me wave them in so they can come help Mommy, okay?
Okay, you'll have to help me listen for the ambulance. What's your mommy's name?
That's okay. We're going to help her. Can you go open the front door for me so we can listen for the ambulance?
Are you by the door so I can hear the ambulance?
Okay, listen for the sirens with me, okay?
You're a very smart little girl for calling me so we can get your mommy help. What's your last name?
I don't feel good. Mommy doesn't feel good.
That's right, and you're a very smart little girl for calling me so we can get her help. Can you wave at the ambulance when you see them?
Yes, there's a small child at the door.
